# Build context ignore rules for docker/Dockerfile.dev ONLY.
#
# BuildKit automatically uses this file instead of the repo-root .dockerignore
# when the build targets this Dockerfile (`-f docker/Dockerfile.dev`).
# It fully replaces the root .dockerignore (no merge).
#
# Unlike the other tailored ignores, Dockerfile.dev builds Matterbridge from
# LOCAL source (multi-stage) and stamps the version from git
# (scripts/version.mjs git). It therefore MUST keep .git, scripts/, src/,
# packages/ and apps/ — so those are intentionally NOT listed here.
# We only drop trees no build step reads.

# Matter spec HTML — reference only, never read by any build step (~84 MB)
chip

# Local tooling / editor / agent dirs
.agents
.claude
.devcontainer
.env
.github
**/.cache/
**/.vscode/

# systemd unit files — not used by the build (the builder deletes them anyway)
systemd

# Dependencies (regenerated by npm ci)
**/node_modules/

# Test and build output (rebuilt inside the image)
**/coverage/
**/dist/
**/build/
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# Logs
**/*.log
**/npm-debug.log*
**/yarn-debug.log*
**/pnpm-debug.log*

# Other assets not needed for builds
docs
reflector
screenshots
tmp
jest
**/tmp/
**/*.tgz
